<title>USA: Phillips-Van sees short-term earnings hurt.</title>
<headline>Phillips-Van sees short-term earnings hurt.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-03-10</dateline>
<text>
<p>Phillips-Van Heusen Corp said on Monday it will increase its spending on marketing by $20 million in the coming year, with the result that short-term earnings growth will be &quot;restrained.&quot;</p>
<p>The company said it will invest a total of $40 million to market its brands this year. While that could have an impact on short-term earnings, the company expects the long-term benefits to be significant.</p>
